data.title: Frank Castillo
data.meta_description: Frank Castillo. Self: Sunday Night Baseball. Frank Castillo was born on 1 April 1969 in El Paso, Texas, USA. He died on 28 July 2013 in Bartlett Lake, Arizona, USA.
data.text:
Pitcher selected by the Chicago Cubs in the 6th round of the 1987 amateur draft out of Eastwood High Sschool (El Paso, TX). Played for the Cubs (1991-97), Colorado Rockies (1997), Detroit Tigers (1998), Toronto Blue Jays (2000), Boston Red Sox (2001-02 and 2004), and Florida Marlins (2005).

Given a World Series ring by the 2004 Boston Red Sox despite appearing in just 2 games that season.
